BaseFalconSwerve (and most other swerve templates) will check that the speed of the desired state is above some threshold before steering the wheel, since you usually never want to steer a stopped wheel.

There are a few ways around this, what I did was probably a bit janky but it works. Basically I added a steerWhenStill boolean parameter that will bypass the check in the swerve module setDesiredState() . Here’s the code:

